			"body": "<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: summarize by coderabbit.ai -->\nNo actionable comments were generated in the recent review. 🎉\n\n<details>\n<summary>ℹ️ Recent review info</summary>\n\n**Configuration used**: Path: .coderabbit.yaml\n\n**Review profile**: CHILL\n\n**Plan**: Pro\n\n<details>\n<summary>📥 Commits</summary>\n\nReviewing files that changed from the base of the PR and between 259e0a639eeca1dfdb509b3f62cf59e3c6d24305 and 78712770000db704a55991d858b70d92992200c8.\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>📒 Files selected for processing (2)</summary>\n\n* `packages/app-desktop/gui/note-viewer/index.html`\n* `packages/app-desktop/integration-tests/markdownEditor.spec.ts`\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚧 Files skipped from review as they are similar to previous changes (1)</summary>\n\n* packages/app-desktop/gui/note-viewer/index.html\n\n</details>\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n\n<!-- walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>📝 Walkthrough</summary>\n\n## Walkthrough\n\nReworks search highlighting in the markdown preview to use the CSS Highlights API: collects per-match Ranges into `allRanges`, creates a `Highlight` named `\"search-results\"` from those ranges and stores it on `CSS.highlights`, clears prior highlights at start of `setMarkers`, and adds a `::highlight(search-results)` CSS rule.\n\n## Changes\n\n|Cohort / File(s)|Summary|\n|---|---|\n|**Search Results Highlighting** <br> `packages/app-desktop/gui/note-viewer/index.html`|Adds `allRanges` accumulation and per-match `each` callback to collect Ranges; clears previous CSS highlights at start of `setMarkers`; constructs `new Highlight(allRanges)` and assigns it to `CSS.highlights[\"search-results\"]`; updates `markKeyword` call to pass `{ element: 'mark-ghost', each: ... }`; adds `::highlight(search-results)` CSS rule; minor formatting/logic reorganisation.|\n|**Integration Test update** <br> `packages/app-desktop/integration-tests/markdownEditor.spec.ts`|Adjusts local search test to count `mark-ghost` elements instead of `mark` to match the new highlighting element class.|\n\n## Suggested labels\n\n`bug`, `desktop`, `search`\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 5</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (5 passed)</summary>\n\n|         Check name         | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                           |\n| :------------------------: | :------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n|         Title check        | ✅ Passed | The title clearly describes the main change: fixing the issue where search highlights are included when copying from markdown preview.                                                |\n|      Description check     | ✅ Passed | The description is directly related to the changeset, explaining the root cause, the fix using CSS Custom Highlight API, and providing testing steps.                                 |\n|     Linked Issues check    | ✅ Passed | The code changes successfully address the linked issue `#12385` by migrating from mark.js DOM insertion to CSS Custom Highlight API, eliminating search highlights from copied content. |\n| Out of Scope Changes check | ✅ Passed | All changes are directly related to fixing issue `#12385`: the note-viewer highlights implementation and the corresponding test update are both within scope.                           |\n|     Docstring Coverage     | ✅ Passed | No functions found in the changed files to evaluate docstring coverage. Skipping docstring coverage check.                                                                            |\n\n</details>\n\n<sub>✏️ Tip: You can configure your